Tun MonAL. Oh ! gentle readers! let me lay before ye A moral, drawn from this veracious story. Do not go through woods at night! Do not with your neighbours fight ! Do not ride a horse that's frisky! Don't quaff copious draughts of whiskey ! And if anything ail you, Or if your strength fail you, And the fever should “ nail” you, Don’t take those drugs which old women concoct, or You’ll soon repent it ; but send for the doctor!
